    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Peel and cut your <strong>shallot[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>shallot wedges</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until slightly softened and beginning to caramelise</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sausage-pea-and-courgette-stew/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the shallots are cooking, cut your <strong>sausages</strong> into thirds</p><p>Once slightly softened, add the<strong> sausages pieces</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sausage-pea-and-courgette-stew/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> into quarters</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> in 250ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>mustardy stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sausage-pea-and-courgette-stew/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the<strong> </strong>sausages have browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour </strong>and cook for 1 min further or until the flour has dissolved</p><p>Reduce the heat to medium and add the<strong> chopped potatoes</strong> and<strong> mustardy stock </strong>with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and cook, covered, for 20-22 min or until the potatoes are fork tender and sausages are cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sausage-pea-and-courgette-stew/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the<strong> </strong>potatoes<strong> </strong>are cooking, slice your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> lengthways, then slice on a diagonal into 1cm thick slices</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sausage-pea-and-courgette-stew/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes<strong> </strong>are fork tender, add the <strong>sliced courgette</strong> to the pan</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook, covered, for a further 4-5 min or until the courgette is tender with a slight bite</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sausage-pea-and-courgette-stew/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add your<strong> blanched peas</strong> and <strong>soft cheese</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook, uncovered, for 1 min further \u2013 this is your<strong> creamy sausage, pea & courgette stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sausage-pea-and-courgette-stew/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy sausage, pea & courgette stew</strong> and season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
